Russia’s Grain Output May Expand for Next 3 Years, Ministry Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-09-22T11:56:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/russia-s-grain-output-may-expand-for-next-3-years-ministry-says.html
Russia’s grain crop will expand for
the next three years after jumping 51 percent this year to 91.9
million metric tons, the  Economy Ministry  said.  Grain production may increase 1.6 percent in 2012 and 2013
and 5.3 percent in 2014, the ministry said in a report on its
website. The sunflower seed crop will drop 12 percent next year
after rising 45 percent this year, it said.  Meat and meat products output is expected to rise 8 percent
this year, 6.9 percent in 2012 and 5.4 percent in 2013, it said.  Russia’s agricultural sector will contribute between
3.2 percent to 3.3 percent of gross domestic product in the next
three years, the ministry forecast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
